.TH "reallocate_resource" 9 "reallocate_resource" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reallocate_resource \- allocate a slot in the resource tree given range & alignment. The resource will be relocated if the new size cannot be reallocated in the current location.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" reallocate_resource
.BI "(struct resource *root "  ","
.BI "struct resource *old "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t newsize "  ","
.BI "struct resource_constraint *constraint "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "root" 12
root resource descriptor
.IP "old" 12
resource descriptor desired by caller
.IP "newsize" 12
new size of the resource descriptor
.IP "constraint" 12
the size and alignment constraints to be met.
